data.description: Enchanting river views mesmerize from the front porch and from many rooms of this charming Victorian in the heart of downtown Nyack. This home would shine even more brightly with a loving restoration. Cared for since 1965 by a family who raised nine children here, this home was loved like no other. The feeling of welcoming and happy memories fill the walls and they would love someone to help continue her legacy. Located across from the Hudson, a block from waterfront Memorial Park and close to shops, restaurants, commuting options, hiking, and biking trails.
